<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-18-0631 </DOCNO><TEXT>Despite attractive prices, the heavy gas oil market continues to be sluggish.This lack of sales raises a problem for oil refiners since the productionof heavy gas oil, an inevitable by-product, increases proportionallyto that of the light oils, for which demand is rising. Why does industryshun the heavy gas oil. In this paper consumers express their concernover the development of product characteristics and future regulationof environmental pollution. Oil producers demonstrate the financial andstrategic advantages of heavy gas oil.</TEXT></DOC>